## 🚀 Installation

1. Install [Tampermonkey](https://www.tampermonkey.net/) for your browser
2. Click **Install** on this page
3. Open [YouTube](https://www.youtube.com/) — a 🔍 button will appear in the top bar next to your avatar
4. Left-click 🔍 to open the management panel

---

## 📖 How to Use

### Adding a channel to the blocklist
**Method A — Panel**
1. Click 🔍 in the top bar → open panel → **🚫 Blocklist** tab
2. Click **＋ Add** → enter channel name or @handle → click **Confirm**

**Method B — Quick button (fastest)**
- Hover over any video card on the homepage or sidebar
- Click the 🚫 button that appears on the thumbnail

**Method C — Channel page**
- Visit the channel's YouTube page
- Click **🚫 Block this channel** in the channel header

### Removing a channel from the blocklist
- Open **🚫 Blocklist** tab → click **✕** next to the channel name
- An inline confirmation row appears → click **Confirm removal**

### Keyword filtering
1. Open panel → **🔤 Keywords** tab
2. Click **＋ New Group** → enter a group name → set scope (Title / Description) → **Create**
3. Click **＋ Keyword** on the group → type a keyword or Regex → press **Enter** or click **Add**
4. Toggle the group switch to enable/disable without deleting

### Language filtering
1. Open panel → **⚙️ Filters** tab → enable **🌐 Language Filter**
2. Choose mode: **Block selected languages** or **Show only selected languages**
3. Check the preset languages or enter custom BCP-47 codes (e.g. `th, vi, id`)
4. Click **💾 Save Settings**

### Exporting & sharing
- **Export**: panel → **💾 Export/Import** tab → choose JSON or CSV format
- **Share**: panel → **💾 Export/Import** → **Share Filter List** section → choose what to share → copy the generated link and send it to a friend

### Keyboard shortcuts (Tampermonkey menu)
| Action | How |
|--------|-----|
| Open panel | Click 🔍 in top bar, or Tampermonkey menu → ⚙️ Open Panel |
| Toggle filter | Right-click 🔍, or Tampermonkey menu → 🔄 Toggle Filter |
| Manual backup | Tampermonkey menu → 💾 Backup Now |

